5	[Continuation].   Now, Kide was not your ordinary snake; he had a peculiar fascination with fashion. While most snakes were content slithering through the grass in their natural state, Kide had a grand vision of becoming the most stylish serpent in the animal kingdom.  Kide's journey into the world of fashion began when he found an abandoned shoelace in the forest. With great determination, he managed to tie the shoelace around his neck as a makeshift tie. The forest creatures couldn't believe their eyes as Kide proudly displayed his new "accessory."  Soon, word of Kide's fashion sense spread throughout the animal kingdom. Animals from near and far came to see the stylish snake. Kide became a fashion icon, and he embraced his new role wholeheartedly. He experimented with scarves, belts, and even a top hat he found discarded by a nearby hiker.  One day, a wise old owl visited Kide and said, "Kide, fashion is not just about looking good; it's about expressing your unique self." Kide pondered these words, realizing that he had become so consumed with his outward appearance that he had neglected the qualities that truly mattered.  Determined to embrace both style and substance, Kide started hosting fashion shows that promoted eco-friendly and sustainable clothing made from materials found in the forest. He also organized clean-up events to keep the forest beautiful and safe for all creatures.  Kide's transformation from a fashion-obsessed snake to a thoughtful and responsible community leader was truly inspiring. His fashion sense continued to turn heads, but now it was his heart, kindness, and commitment to a better environment that made him a true icon in the animal kingdom.  And so, Kide, the once-fashion-obsessed snake, became a symbol of the perfect blend of style, substance, and caring for the world around us, teaching everyone that true beauty goes beyond appearances and lies within the heart.	2023-11-04 21:26:06.563996+00	2023-11-04 21:26:06.564012+00	4	2
